      "description": "This 2017 Ford Focus RS is a meticulously maintained performance hatch featuring the 2.3L EcoBoost engine with its signature twin-scroll turbocharger and high-flow cylinder head. The mechanical highlight is the GKN Twinster all-wheel-drive system, which utilizes dual-clutch packs at the rear axle for active torque vectoring, ensuring exceptional lateral grip and neutral handling characteristics. The short-throw 6-speed manual transmission shifts with precision, and the factory-equipped Brembo four-piston monoblock calipers provide firm, fade-resistant deceleration. Suspension remains tight with functional dual-mode adjustable dampers. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina expected of a well-loved driver, the powertrain and drivetrain are in excellent health, with consistent maintenance intervals documented for the Power Transfer Unit (PTU) and rear drive unit. It currently rides on lightweight forged alloy wheels, offering a significant reduction in unsprung mass for improved steering response.",
